{
  "texts": [
    "Modern neural network architectures (such as Transformer) create relationships between words and sentences in a language [84,88].",
    "To increase the probability that the model will be selected in the next sentence in the context, the training process tries to identify negative aspects of the model [88].",
    "It is common practice to use stochastic gradient descent (SGD) to achieve this goal.",
    "Backpropagation is then used to update the parameters of the model containing the back computation gradients.",
    "Learns from multiple objective feedbacks at every level of training."
  ]
}